title: Loki pranks you Pt 2
body:
You were determined to get Loki back after the last prank that he pulled on you. He cut the power to your house and pretended to be an intruder and scared you. He will regret that decision. You had the perfect idea. Instead of one large prank, you would set up multiple small pranks. You went to your laptop to lookup some ideas. Once you had the pranks planned, you had to run to the store before he got home. You ran to grab your keys and wallet. You headed out the front door to your car, locking the door behind you. You had to get whipped cream, feathers, plastic wrap, water balloons, and silly string. You went to the closest store to grab the essential items and were headed back home in no time.

You had to makes sure that you hid the items where Loki wouldn’t find them, and that place was the closet in the guest bedroom, he never looked in there. As soon as you closed the door to the closet, you heard the front door open. It was Loki.  You went to greet him.

“Hey, how are you doing” you say, greeting him with a kiss, trying to not look too suspicious.

“I’m exhausted.  Training with Thor always makes me so tired” he replied. You saw your opportunity.

“Why don’t you go take a nap? I will cook us dinner, how about spaghetti?”

“Are you sure (y/n)? I feel bad not helping you.”

“It’s okay! You are exhausted, you deserve a nap” you reply, trying your hardest for him to take a nap so you can set up your plan.

“You are the best, darling. What would I do without you?” he says, hugging you, then walking to the bedroom that you shared, closing the door.

As soon as the door clicked, you ran to the guest bedroom to get the supplies. You started to set up the pranks. You ran to the garage to grab a bucket. You took that and the water balloons outside to start filling them up. After the bucket was full to the top of water balloons, you carried them to the back yard and sat them down in. You ran back inside and took the silly string out of the bag and placed it on the kitchen table.

Next, you took the plastic wrap and placed it on the door of the bedroom, making sure that it was at appropriate level to ensure that Loki would run face first into it. Now was the tricky part. You had the whipped cream and feather in hand. You quietly opened the door to the room, hearing Loki lightly snoring. ‘Good, he’s asleep’ you thought to yourself. You snuck over to the side of the bed that he was laying on, noting that he left one hand open, slightly off the side of the bed. This was perfect. You opened the can of whipped cream, and as quietly as you could, sprayed a large amount of cream into his hand. You had to put your hand over your mouth to quiet your giggles. You took the feather and lightly tickled his nose.

Splat

He took the hand that was full of whipped cream, and went to scratch his nose, getting whipped cream all over his face. The look on his face was priceless.

“(Y/N)!” Loki yelled, as you bolted out of the room. He went to chase after you, but he did not notice the plastic wrap over the door frame and slammed into it. He was disoriented for a few seconds, giving you enough time to run into the kitchen to grab the silly string.

“(Y/N), get back here!” He yelled with a smile tugging at the corners of his mouth. The second that he stepped into the kitchen, you started to douse him with silly string.

“This is what you get for scaring me to death!” you yell at him, running to the back door. Loki was hot on your trail. You used up all of the silly string, and threw the can on the ground, sprinting towards the water balloons. As soon as you saw Loki, you immediately started throwing the balloons at him. He held up his are defensively, trying to shield himself from the balloons, but it was doing no good. He was getting drenched. All of the sudden, you saw Loki disappear ‘Shit, I didn’t even thing of that’ you thought to yourself. You heard a noise behind you, and before you could react, Loki had a water balloon in his hand, and threw it at you. You started running for the door to the house, but Loki appeared in front of you out of thin air.

“You’re not getting out of this that easy, (y/n). He said before hitting you with another water balloon. He was chasing you all over the yard, throwing what was left of the water balloons at you. When the bucket was empty, he pulled you into a hug. He was covered in whipped cream, silly string and water.

“I must admit (y/n), you got me pretty good. I did not see any of that coming” he says. “But you do know, that this means war”.
